  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Controlling the glycemic impact of foodstuffs (by reducing the glycemic load of the diet by
      using soluble dietary fibres) may reduce the glycemic or insulinemic response. This may in
      turn result in a reduced inhibition of postprandial fat oxidation rate and a lower plasma
      triacylglycerol concentration A higher postprandial fat oxidation may result in less lipid
      accumulation in non-adipose tissue thereby improving insulin sensitivity and the metabolic
      profile in the longer term.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
